==Description== This template is used to insert descriptions on template pages. ==Syntax== Add {{t|Documentation}} at the end of the template page. Add {{t|Documentation|documentation page}} to transclude an alternative page from the /doc subpage. ==Usage== ===On the Template page=== This is the normal format when used: 
TEMPLATE CODE
Any categories to be inserted into articles by the template
{{Documentation}}
''If your template is not a completed div or table, you may need to close the tags just before {{Documentation}} is inserted (within the noinclude tags).'' ''A line break right before {{Documentation}} can also be useful as it helps prevent the documentation template "running into" previous code.'' ===On the documentation page=== The documentation page is usually located on the /doc subpage for a template, but a different page can be specified with the first parameter of the template (see [[#Syntax|Syntax]]). Normally, you will want to write something like the following on the documentation page: 
==Description==
This template is used to do something.

==Syntax==
Type {{t|templatename}} somewhere.

==Samples==
<nowiki>{{templatename|input}}</nowiki> 

results in...

{{templatename|input}}

Any categories for the template itself
[[Category:Template documentation]]
Use any or all of the above description/syntax/sample output sections. You may also want to add "see also" or other sections. Note that the above example also uses the [[Template:T]] template. [[Category:Documentation templates]][[Category:Template documentation]]

;Description :This template is used to create a basic navigation box. You can do so by calling the template, via the steps under "Syntax", but it is recommended to '''copy the code verbatim''' via the steps under "Navbox Creation". ;Navbox Creation type=create prefix=Template: preload=Template:Navbox_Sample editintro=Template:Navbox/doc buttonlabel=Make your navbox! default = Navbox Foo #Think of a name for your navbox, like "Navbox Foo". Type it in the above field, press the button, and save the page immediately. Be ready to return to ''this'' page to see the rest of the instructions. #Edit the resulting page in source mode. #Replace {{{header}}} with the text you would like to appear in the header. #Replace {{{body}}} with the text you would like to appear in the body. #To add another section, copy these four lines of code immediately below the lines in the existing code that they resemble: 
|-
! style="padding:0.2em 0.5em;" nowrap="nowrap" class="color1" | {{{header}}}
|-
| style="padding:0.2em 0.5em;" | {{{body}}}
Save the page once you have added as many sections as you needed, and filled them with content. You may also want to create a /doc subpage explaining that to call the resulting template, one must only type {{Navbox Foo}}, or rather, whatever we decided to name the template in step 1. ;Syntax 
{{navbox
|header=Land of Bob
|body=This [[place]] and that [[place]].
}}
:Results in... {{navbox |header=Land of Bob |body=This [[place]] and that [[place]]. }} [[Category:Navbox templates]][[Category:Template documentation]]

== Description == This template uses your wiki's SITENAME and strips off the word "wiki" leaving what is in most cases the text describing the topic of your wiki. To use this template in its basic form, simply add the {{T|{{BASEPAGENAME}}}} template wherever you want your topic to appear in a sentence or section. If your wiki's SITENAME minus the word "wiki" is not a good descriptor for your wiki's topic, you may also simply edit the template and replace it with just the text you want displayed. == Syntax == 
{{Topic}}
== Sample output == {{Topic}} [[Category:Templates]][[Category:Template documentation|{{PAGENAME}}]]

{{t|Dialogue}} facilitates the writing of dialogue in a standard format. The template can handle most standard formats of writing dialogue, and can be indented, bulleted or numbered. '''This template ''cannot'' be subst:'d'''. This template uses the [[w:Help:Lua|Lua templating language]], and more information can be found [[w:c:dev:Global_Lua_Modules/Dialogue|on the Global Lua Module page]]. '''For a traditional wikitext version of this template, see [[w:c:templates:Template:Dialogue/wikitext|Dialogue on Templates Wiki]]'''. ==Syntax== This is how to write the template in [[w:Help:wikitext|wikitext]] onto your article: 
{{dialogue
|short=full
|short=full
|short=full
...
|Character|Speech
|Character|Speech
|Character|Speech
...
|cite = dialogue description
}}
These parameters are explained more fully below. ==Parameters== '''Named parameters specify name shortcuts. They are all optional.''' They are placed at the top of the template call, like this: 
{{dialogue
|short=full
|short=full
|short=full
...
Name shortcuts apply to your main dialogue text. If you use a shortcut specified here for a character name, then the full name will be replaced for it. Named parameters of the form "mood1", "mood2", "mood3", etc., up to "mood10", specify moods for the corresponding line number (e.g. "mood1" specifies line 1). They are placed in a line like this: 
...
|Character|Speech|mood1=angry
|Character|Speech|mood2=quiet
|Character|Speech|mood3=ecstatic
...
Positional parameters form the text of the dialogue (i.e. any line not containing an "=" will be construed as part of the dialogue. :;Parameter 1 ''(required)'' : Character name speaking :;Parameter 2 ''(optional)'' : Line to speak :;Parameter 3 ''(optional)'' : Next character :;Parameter 4 ''(optional)'' : Next line :;Parameter 5 ''(optional)'' : Next character :;Parameter 6 ''(optional)'' : Next line :;Parameter 7 ''(optional)'' : so on... Note: if any character is called "action" then that line will be construed as an action line. It still counts as a ''line'' nonetheless. To write a dialogue description/source, use cite = ==Examples== Here is an example of a full template usage: 
{{dialogue
|harry=Harry Enfield
|bryan=Bryan Adams

|harry|Hello!                |mood1=happy
|bryan|Oh hello there        |mood2=surprised
|harry|How are you?          |mood3=inquisitive
|bryan|Quite fine thank you. |mood4=reserved
|harry|Oh that's spiffing.   |mood5=spiffed
|bryan|It is, isn't it?!     |mood6=multo-spiffed
|harry|Quite so.             |mood7=bored
|bryan|Well, I'm off!        |mood8=joyous
|harry|Ta-ta!                |mood9=relieved
|bryan|Au revoir!            |mood10=sarcastic
}}
The above would generate: {{dialogue |harry=Harry Enfield |bryan=Bryan Adams |harry|Hello! |mood1=happy |bryan|Oh hello there |mood2=surprised |harry|How are you? |mood3=inquisitive |bryan|Quite fine thank you. |mood4=reserved |harry|Oh that's spiffing. |mood5=spiffed |bryan|It is, isn't it?! |mood6=multo-spiffed |harry|Quite so. |mood7=bored |bryan|Well, I'm off! |mood8=joyous |harry|Ta-ta! |mood9=relieved |bryan|Au revoir! |mood10=sarcastic }} The below code demonstrates examples of extended use: 
{{dialogue
|george=Georgie Boy
|rachel=Rachel

|action|Enter: George and Rachel
|george|Good morrow dearest Rachel!|mood2=happy
|action|Rachel turns to see him
|rachel|Oh, George, it's you!
|george|...
|rachel|Why won't you say anything?!|mood6=worried
|action|Enter: Guards
|Guards|We are announcing George's arrest!
|rachel|Oh my!|mood9=horrified
|action|George is dragged away.
}}
The above would generate: {{dialogue |george=Georgie Boy |rachel=Rachel |action|Enter: George and Rachel |george|Good morrow dearest Rachel!|mood2=happy |action|Rachel turns to see him |rachel|Oh, George, it's you! |george|... |rachel|Why won't you say anything?!|mood6=worried |action|Enter: Guards |Guards|We are announcing George's arrest! |rachel|Oh my!|mood9=horrified |action|George is dragged away. }} ===Notes=== You can number, bullet or indent your dialogue: 
:{{dialogue|Me|Hello|You|Howdido!}}
:{{dialogue|Me|Hello|You|Howdido!}} 
#{{dialogue|Me|Hello|You|Howdido!}}
#{{dialogue|Them|Good afternoon|Us|What a load of rubbish!}}
#{{dialogue|Me|Hello|You|Howdido!}} #{{dialogue|Them|Good afternoon|Us|What a load of rubbish!}} 
*{{dialogue
|angel=Fortitude
|angel|I am an angel!|Crowd|We don't believe you!}}
*{{dialogue
|angel=Fortitude
|angel|But I'm being quite serious!|Crowd|Too bad for you then!}}
*{{dialogue |angel=Fortitude |angel|I am an angel!|Crowd|We don't believe you!}} *{{dialogue |angel=Fortitude |angel|But I'm being quite serious!|Crowd|Too bad for you then!}} You will get the odd spacing error (e.g. "Speech") if you lay out your dialogue on multiple lines. This is the {{t|Namespace}} meta-template. It helps other templates detect what type of page they are on. It detects and groups all the different [[Wikipedia:Namespace#Enumeration|namespaces]] used on Fandom into several types: ; main : Main (i.e. article) space, where normal articles are kept. ; talk : Any talk space, including page names that start with "Talk:", "User talk:", "File talk:", etc. ;user ;file ;mediawiki ;template ;help ;category : The remaining namespaces. ; other : Any namespaces that were not specified as a parameter to the template (see explanation below). For backwards compatibility, this template handles '''image''' as if '''file'''. '''image''' ([[Image:...]]) is now deprecated. '''Note:''' For most cases it may be better to use the simpler namespace detection templates (see the [[#See also|see also]] section below). This template is more prone to human errors such as misspelling parameter names. This template uses the [[w:Help:Lua|Lua templating language]], and more information can be found [[w:c:dev:Global_Lua_Modules/Namespace_detect|on the Global Lua Module page]]. '''For a traditional wikitext version of this template, see [[w:c:templates:Template:Namespace_detect|Namespace_detect on Templates Wiki]]'''. == Usage == This template takes one or more parameters named after the different page types as listed above. Like this: 
{{Namespace
 | main  = Article text
 | talk  = Talk page text
 | other = Other pages text
}}
If the template is on a main (article) page, it will return this: : {{Namespace |demospace=main | main = Article text | talk = Talk page text | other = Other pages text }} If the template is on any other page than an article or a talk page, it will return this: : {{Namespace | main = Article text | talk = Talk page text | other = Other pages text }} The example above made the template return something for all page types. But if we don't use the '''other''' parameter or leave it empty, it will not return anything for the other page types. Like this: 
{{Namespace
 | file     = File page text
 | category = Category page text
 | other    =
}}
On any pages other than file and category pages the code above will render nothing. : {{Namespace | file = File page text | category = Category page text | other = }} By using an empty parameter, you can make it so the template doesn't render anything for some specific page type. Like this: 
{{Namespace
 | main  = 
 | other = Other pages text
}}
The code above will render nothing when on mainspace (article) pages, but will return this when on other pages: : {{Namespace | main = | other = Other pages text }} == Demospace and page == For testing and demonstration purposes, this template can take two parameters named '''demospace''' and '''page'''. '''demospace''' understands any of the page type names used by this template, including the '''other''' type. It tells the template to behave like it is on some specific type of page. Like this: 
{{Namespace
 | main  = Article text
 | other = Other pages text
 | demospace = main
}}
No matter on what kind of page the code above is used, it will return this: : {{Namespace | main = Article text | other = Other pages text | demospace = main }} The '''page''' parameter instead takes a normal pagename, making this template behave exactly as if on that page. The pagename doesn't have to be an existing page. Like this: 
{{Namespace
 | user  = User page text
 | other = Other pages text
 | page  = User:Example
}}
No matter on what kind of page the code above is used, it will return this: : {{Namespace | user = User page text | other = Other pages text | page = User:Example }} It can be convenient to let your template understand the '''demospace''' and/or '''page''' parameter and send it on to the {{T|Namespace}} template. Like this: 
{{Namespace
 | main  = Article text
 | other = Other pages text
 | demospace = {{{demospace|}}}
 | page  = {{{page|}}}
}}
If both the '''demospace''' and '''page''' parameters are empty or undefined, the template will detect page types as usual. == Parameters == List of all parameters: 
{{Namespace
| main  = 
...
| other =
| demospace = {{{demospace|}}} / main / talk / user /
              file / mediawiki / template /
              help / category / other
| page  = {{{page|}}} / User:Example
}}
== Technical details == If you intend to feed tables as content to the numbered parameters of this template, you need to know this: [[w:Help:Template|Templates]] have a problem handling parameter data that contains pipes "|" unless the pipe is inside another template {{name|param1}} or inside a piped link [[w:Help:Template|help]]. Thus templates can not handle [[w:Help:Table|wikitables]] as input unless you escape them by using the {{!}} [[w:Help:Magic words|magic word]]. This makes it hard to use wikitables as parameters to templates. Instead, the usual solution is to use HTML wikimarkup for the table code, which is more robust. [[Category:General wiki templates]]{{#ifeq:{{SUBPAGENAME}}|sandbox|[[Category:Namespace manipulation templates]]}}[[Category:Template documentation]]

-- This Module is used for making templates based in the Lua language. -- See more details about Lua in [[w:Help:Lua]]. -- The Fandom Developer's Wiki hosts Global Lua Modules that can be imported and locally overridden. -- The next line imports the Mbox module from the [[w:c:dev:Global Lua Modules]]. local Mbox = require('Dev:Mbox') -- See more details about this module at [[w:c:dev:Global_Lua_Modules/Mbox]]
-- The imported Module is overwritten locally to include default styling. -- For a more flexible Mbox experience, delete the function below and import -- https://dev.fandom.com/wiki/MediaWiki:Global_Lua_Modules/Mbox.css -- or paste (and modify as you like) its contents in your wiki's -- [[MediaWiki:Wikia.css]] (see [[w:Help:Including_additional_CSS_and_JS]]) -- or look at https://dev.fandom.com/wiki/Global_Lua_Modules/Mbox -- for more customization inspiration
-- -- BEGIN DELETION HERE --
local getArgs = require('Dev:Arguments').getArgs local localCSS = mw.loadData('Module:Mbox/data').localStyle
function Mbox.main(frame) local args = getArgs(frame)
-- styles local styles = {} if args.bordercolor then styles['border-left-color'] = args.bordercolor elseif args.type then styles['border-left-color'] = 'var(--type-' .. args.type .. ')' end
if args.bgcolor then styles['background-color'] = args.bgcolor end
-- images local image = args.image or '' local imagewidth = args.imagewidth or '80px' local imagelink = '' if args.imagelink then imagelink = '|link=' .. args.imagelink end
local imagewikitext = ('%sFile:%s|%s%s' .. ']]'):format('[[', image, imagewidth, imagelink)
-- id for closure local id = args.id or 'mbox'
local container = mw.html.create('div') :addClass('mbox') :addClass(args.class) :css(styles) :css(localCSS['mbox']) :cssText(args.style)
local content = container:tag('div') :addClass('mbox__content') :css(localCSS['mbox__content'])
if args.image then local image = content:tag('div') :addClass('mbox__content__image') :addClass('mw-collapsible') :attr('id', 'mw-customcollapsible-' .. id) :css(localCSS['mbox__content__image']) :wikitext(imagewikitext) if args.collapsed then image:addClass('mw-collapsed') end end
local contentwrapper = content:tag('div') :addClass('mbox__content__wrapper') :css(localCSS['mbox__content__wrapper'])
if args.header then contentwrapper:tag('div') :addClass('mbox__content__header') :css(localCSS['mbox__content__header']) :wikitext(args.header) end
if args.text then local text = contentwrapper:tag('div') :addClass('mbox__content__text') :addClass('mw-collapsible') :attr('id', 'mw-customcollapsible-' .. id) :css(localCSS['mbox__content__text']) :wikitext(args.text) if args.collapsed then text:addClass('mw-collapsed') end
if args.comment then text:tag('div') :addClass('mbox__content__text__comment') :css(localCSS['mbox__content__text__comment']) :wikitext(args.comment) end end
contentwrapper:tag('span') :addClass('mbox__close') :addClass('mw-customtoggle-' .. id) :css(localCSS['mbox__close']) :attr('title', 'Dismiss')
if args.aside then local aside = content:tag('div') :addClass('mbox__content__aside') :addClass('mw-collapsible') :attr('id', 'mw-customcollapsible-' .. id) :css(localCSS['mbox__content__aside']) :wikitext(args.aside) if args.collapsed then aside:addClass('mw-collapsed') end end
return container end
-- -- END DELETION HERE --
-- The last line produces the output for the template return Mbox

;Description This template allows you to clear the left side, right side, or both sides of the page. Clearing means that the content following the template will not be displayed until the existing content on the specified sides (for example, "hanging" or floating images or blocks) is displayed completely. This template is often used so that the text does not flow around unrelated images. The template adds the following code to the page:
(the value after clear depends on the parameters). This code affects elements with the CSS property float, including files floated to the side (for example, [[File:Image.png|right]]). ;Syntax * To clear both sides of the page, add the code {{t|Clear}}. * To clear only the left side of the page, add the code {{t|Clear|left}}. * To clear only the right side of the page, add the code {{t|Clear|right}}. You can also use {{t|-}} instead of {{t|Clear}} as a shorthand call for this template. __NOTOC__ ;Example 

=== Section 1 ===
[[File:Example.jpg|200px|right]]
Section 1 text.

=== Section 2 ===
Section 2 text.
{{Clear|right}}

=== Section 3 ===
Section 3 text.
This code produces the following result: ---- === Section 1 === [[File:Example.jpg|200px|right]] Section 1 text. === Section 2 === Section 2 text. {{Clear|right}} === Section 3 === Section 3 text. ---- As you can see above, the example image added in section 1 is displayed to the right and extends down through section 2, while the {{t|Clear}} template is called at the end of the second section, resulting in the example image not being next to section 3. Thus, one use of the {{t|Clear}} template is to control which elements are displayed next to which other elements. == See also == * [https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/clear CSS property clear on MDN] * [https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/float CSS property float on MDN] [[Category:General wiki templates]][[Category:Template documentation]]

== Description == To use this template, add the {{T|{{BASEPAGENAME}}}} template and fill in the appropriate fields. Fields left blank will not appear in articles. This infobox template uses [[w:Help:Infobox|Fandom's infobox syntax]]. == Syntax == 
{{Game
 | title         = The game's name, displayed on top of the infobox
 | image         = [e.g. "Example.jpg"]
 | developer     = 
 | publisher     = 
 | engine        = The engine the game runs on
 | version       = Most recently released version of the game. If your wiki does patch notes, you may wish to link to those.
 | platform      = Platform(s) the game is available on
 | releasedate   = When the game released
 | genre         = Genre(s) the game is classified as
 | mode          = Singeplayer, multiplayer, etc.
 | rating        = ESRB / PEGI, etc. ratings
 | media         = What media the game is available on (digital, cartridge, cd, etc.)
 | requirements  = System requirements
}}
== Sample output == {{Game | title = The Game of Flower | image = Example.jpg | developer = | publisher = | engine = | version = | platform = PC | releasedate = Soon | genre = RPG | mode = Single player | rating = | media = | requirements = Cutting edge hardware }}

revision.text:
__NOTOC__ This template is used to [[Wikipedia:WP:CITE|cite sources]] in Wikipedia. It is specifically for web sites which are not news sources. This template replaces deprecated [[Wikipedia:Template:Teb reference|template:web reference]]. It provides lower case parameters only. A general discussion of the use of templates for adding citation of open-source web content to Wikipedia articles is available at [[Wikipedia:Citation templates|citation templates]]. This page uses [[w:Wikia:Licensing|Creative Commons Licensed]] content from [[w:c:Wookieepedia:Template:Cite web|Wookieepedia]] == Usage == ;Common form for cases where little is known about authorship of the page (with current date) {{Cite web |url= |title= |accessdate={{CURRENTYEAR}}-{{CURRENTMONTH}}-{{CURRENTDAY2}} |format= |work= }} ;Using last, first (with current date) {{Cite web |url= |title= |accessdate={{CURRENTYEAR}}-{{CURRENTMONTH}}-{{CURRENTDAY2}} |last= |first= |authorlink= |coauthors= |date= |year= |month= |format= |work= |publisher= |pages= |language= |archiveurl= |archivedate= |quote= }} ;Using author (with current date) {{Cite web |url= |title= |accessdate={{CURRENTYEAR}}-{{CURRENTMONTH}}-{{CURRENTDAY2}} |author= |authorlink= |coauthors= |date= |year= |month= |format= |work= |publisher= |pages= |language= |archiveurl= |archivedate= |quote= }} ;Using non-linked retrieved date, last, first {{Cite web |url= |title= |accessmonthday= |accessyear= |last= |first= |authorlink= |coauthors= |date= |year= |month= |format= |work= |publisher= |pages= |language= |archiveurl= |archivedate= |quote= }} ;Using non-linked retrieved date, author {{Cite web |url= |title= |accessmonthday= |accessyear= |author= |authorlink= |coauthors= |date= |year= |month= |format= |work= |publisher= |pages= |language= |archiveurl= |archivedate= |quote= }} ;All parameters, horizontal format (delete the ones you don't need) {{Cite web |url= |title= |accessdate= |accessmonthday= |accessdaymonth = |accessyear= |author= |last= |first= |authorlink= |coauthors= |date= |year= |month= |format= |work= |publisher= |pages= |language= |archiveurl= |archivedate= |quote= }} ;All parameters, vertical format 
{{Cite web
| url = 
| title = 
| accessdate = 
| accessdaymonth = 
| accessmonthday = 
| accessyear = 
| author = 
| last = 
| first = 
| authorlink = 
| coauthors = 
| date = 
| year = 
| month = 
| format = 
| work = 
| publisher = 
| pages = 
| language = 
| archiveurl = 
| archivedate = 
| quote = 
}}
=== Required parameters === * '''url''': URL of online item. * '''title''': Title of online item. ''For producing a [[Wikipedia:WP:CONTEXT#Dates|wikilinked date]] of retrieval:'' :* '''accessdate''': Full date when item was accessed, in [[Wikipedia:ISO 8601|ISO 8601]] YYYY-MM-DD format, for example "accessdate = {{CURRENTYEAR}}-{{CURRENTMONTH}}-{{CURRENTDAY2}}". ''Must not be wikilinked'' ''For producing a non-wikilinked date of retrieval:'' :* '''accessmonthday''' and '''accessyear''': Month and day when item was accessed, for example "accessmonthday = May 10", and year when item was accessed, for example "accessyear = 2005". Produces: ''Retrieved on May 10, 2006.'' :* '''accessdaymonth''' and '''accessyear''': Month and day when item was accessed, for example "accessmonthday = 10 May", and year when item was accessed, for example "accessyear = 2005". Produces: ''Retrieved on 10 May 2006.'' === Optional parameters === * '''author''': Author ** '''last''' works with '''first''' to produce last, first ** '''authorlink''' works either with '''author''' or with '''last''' & '''first''' to link to the appropriate wikipedia article. Does not work with URLs. ** '''coauthors''': allows additional authors * '''date''': Full date of publication, preferably in [[Wikipedia:ISO 8601|ISO 8601]] YYYY-MM-DD format, e.g. ''2006-02-17''. May be wikilinked. ** OR: '''year''': Year of publication, and '''month''': Name of the month of publication. If you also have the day, use ''date'' instead. Must not be wikilinked. * '''format''': Format, e.g. PDF. HTML implied if not specified. * '''work''': If this item is part of a larger work, name of that work. * '''publisher''': Publisher, if any. * '''pages''': ''pp. 57'': first page and optional last page. This is for listing the pages relevant to the citation, not the total number of pages in the book. This is especially useful for PDF format, where the page can be linked to with the #page=''number'' anchor tagged on the end of the URL: *: pages = [http://www.example.org/file.pdf#page=123 p. 123] * '''language''': language of publication (don't specify "English" as this is the default). * '''archiveurl''': URL of the archive location of the item (requires '''archivedate''') * '''archivedate''': Date when the item was archived (requires '''archiveurl'''), in [[Wikipedia:ISO 8601|ISO 8601]] YYYY-MM-DD format, e.g. ''2006-02-17''. Must not be wikilinked; it will be linked automatically. * '''quote''': Relevant quote from online item. == Examples == ;Some standard use cases * {{Cite web | author=Doe, John | title=My Favorite Things Part II | publisher=Open Publishing | date=2005-04-30 | work=Encyclopedia of Things | url=http://www.example.org/ | accessdate=2005-07-06 }}
{{cite web | author=Doe, John | title=My Favorite Things Part II | publisher=Open Publishing | date=2005-04-30 | work=Encyclopedia of Things | url=http://www.example.org | accessdate=2005-07-06 }} * {{Cite web | author=Doe, John | title=My Favorite Things Part II | date=2005-04-30 | work=Encyclopedia of Things | url=http://www.example.org/ | accessdate=2005-07-06 }}
{{cite web | author=Doe, John | title=My Favorite Things Part II | date=2005-04-30 | work=Encyclopedia of Things | url=http://www.example.org | accessdate=2005-07-06 }} * {{Cite web | author=Doe, John | title=My Favorite Things Part II | date=2005-04-30 | url=http://www.example.org/ | accessdate=2005-07-06 }}
{{cite web | author=Doe, John | title=My Favorite Things Part II | date=2005-04-30 | url=http://www.example.org | accessdate=2005-07-06}} * {{Cite web | author=Doe, John | title=My Favorite Things Part II | url=http://www.example.org/ | accessdate=2005-07-06 }}
{{cite web | author=Doe, John | title=My Favorite Things Part II | url=http://www.example.org | accessdate=2005-07-06}} * {{Cite web | title=My Favorite Things Part II | url=http://www.example.org/ | accessdate=2005-07-06 }}
{{cite web | title=My Favorite Things Part II | url=http://www.example.org | accessdate=2005-07-06}} * {{Cite web | url=http://www.nfl.com/fans/ | title=Digest of Rules | publisher= National Football League | accessdate=2005-07-06 }}
{{cite web | url=http://www.nfl.com/fans/ | title=Digest of Rules | publisher= National Football League | accessdate=2005-07-06 }} ;Non-linking date of retrieval (using accessmonthday and accessyear) * {{Cite web | title=My Favorite Things Part II | work=Encyclopedia of Things | url=http://www.example.org/ | accessmonthday=July 6 | accessyear=2005 }}
{{cite web | title=My Favorite Things Part II | work=Encyclopedia of Things | url=http://www.example.org/ | accessmonthday=July 6 | accessyear=2005 }} ;Using format * {{Cite web | title=List of psychotropic substances under international control | publisher = International Narcotics Control Board | url=http://www.incb.org/pdf/e/list/green.pdf | format = PDF | accessdate=2005-07-06 }}
{{cite web | title=List of psychotropic substances under international control | publisher = International Narcotics Control Board | url=http://www.incb.org/pdf/e/list/green.pdf | format = PDF | accessdate=2005-07-06}} ;language * {{Cite web | author=Joliet, Franois | title=Honnit soit qui mal y pense | date=2005-04-30 | url=http://www.example.org/ | accessdate=2005-07-06 | language=French }}
{{cite web | author=Joliet, Franois | title=Honnit soit qui mal y pense | date=2005-04-30 | url=http://www.example.org | accessdate=2005-07-06 | language=French}} ;coauthors * {{Cite web | first=John | last=Doe | coauthors=Peter Smith, Jim Smythe | title=My Favorite Things Part II | publisher=Open Publishing | date=2005-04-30 | work=Encyclopedia of Things | url=http://www.example.org/ | accessdate=2006-05-16 }}
{{cite web | first=John | last=Doe | coauthors=Peter Smith, Jim Smythe | title=My Favorite Things Part II | publisher=Open Publishing | date=2005-04-30 | work=Encyclopedia of Things | url=http://www.example.org/ | accessdate=2006-05-16 }} ;No author * {{Cite web | title=My Favorite Things Part II | publisher=Open Publishing | date=2005-04-30 | work=Encyclopedia of Things | url=http://www.example.org/ | accessdate=2006-05-16 }}
{{cite web | title=My Favorite Things Part II | publisher=Open Publishing | date=2005-04-30 | work=Encyclopedia of Things | url=http://www.example.org/ | accessdate=2006-05-16 }} ;No author, no publisher * {{Cite web | title=My Favorite Things Part II | date=2005-04-30 | work=Encyclopedia of Things | url=http://www.example.org/ | accessdate=2005-07-06 }}
{{cite web | title=My Favorite Things Part II | date=2005-04-30 | work=Encyclopedia of Things | url=http://www.example.org/ | accessdate=2005-07-06 }} * {{Cite web | title=My Favorite Things Part II | date=2005-04-30 | url=http://www.example.org/ | accessdate=2005-07-06 }}
{{cite web | title=My Favorite Things Part II | date=2005-04-30 | url=http://www.example.org/ | accessdate=2005-07-06 }} * {{Cite web | title=List of psychotropic substances under international control | date=2005-04-30 | url=http://www.incb.org/pdf/e/list/green.pdf | format = PDF | accessdate=2005-07-06 | language=Greek }}
{{cite web | title=List of psychotropic substances under international control | date=2005-04-30 | url=http://www.incb.org/pdf/e/list/green.pdf | format = PDF | accessdate=2005-07-06 | language=Greek }} ; Using archiveurl and archivedate to refer to items that went away but are available from an archive site * {{Cite web | title=List of psychotropic substances under international control | date=2005-04-30 | url=http://www.incb.org/pdf/e/list/green.pdf | format = PDF | accessdate=2005-07-06 | archiveurl=http://www.archive.org/2005-09-11/www.incb.org/pdf/e/list/green.pdf | archivedate=2005-09-11 }}
{{cite web | title=List of psychotropic substances under international control | date=2005-04-30 | url=http://www.incb.org/pdf/e/list/green.pdf | format = PDF | accessdate=2005-07-06 | archiveurl=http://www.archive.org/2005-09-11/www.incb.org/pdf/e/list/green.pdf | archivedate=2005-09-11 }} * {{Cite web |url=http://joanjettbadrep.com/cgi-bin/fullStory.cgi?archive=currnews&story=20060405-01shore.htm |title=Interview with Maggie Downs |date=2006-03-31 |publisher=The Desert Sun |archiveurl=http://72.14.207.104/search?q=cache:JAxf4v-pQmgJ:joanjettbadrep.com/cgi-bin/fullStory.cgi%3Farchive%3Dcurrnews%26story%3D20060405-01shore.htm |archivedate=2006-04-26 }}
{{cite web |url=http://joanjettbadrep.com/cgi-bin/fullStory.cgi?archive=currnews&story=20060405-01shore.htm |title=Interview with Maggie Downs |date=2006-03-31 |publisher=The Desert Sun |archiveurl=http://72.14.207.104/search?q=cache:JAxf4v-pQmgJ:joanjettbadrep.com/cgi-bin/fullStory.cgi%3Farchive%3Dcurrnews%26story%3D20060405-01shore.htm |archivedate=2006-04-26}} ; Using quote * {{Cite web | title = My Favorite Things Part II | work = Encyclopedia of Things | url = http://www.example.org/ | accessdate = 2005-07-06 | quote = Lorem ipsum dolor. }}

revision.text: Below is a suggested set of rules to follow when editing this wiki. Administrators of this wiki should read these rules and adapt them as necessary. # Do not copy contents without authorization: All contents, '''especially biography''' published on this site are protected by relevant laws. Do not copy, disseminate or use for other purposes without authorization. Please note that '''information from biography is for use within the site only'''. We reserve the right to take legal responsibility for any violation of this regulation. # '''Keep it civil''': Do not make personal attacks on other people. If you need to criticize another users argument, do so without attacking them as a person. Do not use bigoted language, including slurs which degrade another person or group of people based on gender, race, sexual orientation, nationality, religion, etc. # '''Be a productive member of the wiki''': Contribute to the wiki in line with the established processes and conventions. Need help? Ask an [[Special:ListUsers/sysop|administrator]]! Disrupting the wiki with edit warring over differing opinions of a topic with another user or group of users is not productive. # '''Do not engage in excessive self-promotion''': The wiki is a collaborative community resource for the topic at hand. It is NOT a free place to advertise your related website, YouTube channel, blog, social media account, etc. Have a question about whether your link would be welcome? Ask an administrator! # '''Do not harass other users''': If somebody asks you to stop posting certain content on their wall, respect their wishes. It is their wall. # '''Do follow community guidelines for formatting''': When a community has established formatting, its important to adhere to that, especially when spoiler content is involved. [[Category:{{SITENAME}}]] [[zh:Jiaxing Wiki:]]

[[Jiaxing]] Home is a place for [[Jiaxing]] fans to come together, share their experiences, and engage with others who share their passion. We invite you to join our community and become a part of the conversation. In March 2013, he was admitted to '''[[Hengyang No. 8 Middle School]]''' through the self-enrollment examination, and was admitted to [[Wikipedia:Huazhong University of Science and Technology|Huazhong University of Science and Technology]] through the college entrance examination in 2016. Representative works include "[[Little Apple]]" (2014), "[[The Former You]]", "[[Nineteen Years Old]]", "[[Ordinary Day]]" and so on. ==Life experience== In September 2004, enrolled in Jinwa Primary School in Qidong County. In September 2006, enrolled in Shangshu Primary School in Fengshiyan Town, Qidong County. In September 2010, enrolled in Hengyang Chengzhang Middle School, Qidong Campus, Class 14. In September 2013, enrolled in [[Hengyang No. 8 Middle School]], Class 423. In September 2016, enrolled in Huazhong University of Science and Technology.

'''Wang Zhaochu'''(Chinese name:''''''), born on October 28, 2015 in '''[[Qidong County]], Hengyang City, [[Wikipedia:Hunan|Hunan Province]]''', is the son of '''[[Wang Ximing]]''' and '''[[Lei Yangjuan]]'''. In March 2019, he started studying at Taihetang Little Elves Kindergarten and transferred to [[Qidong County]] Chuyuan Kindergarten (Lianhuayuan) to study in the kindergarten senior class in September 2020. He graduated from Qidong County Chuyuan Kindergarten on July 6, 2021 and started studying at Chuanshan Experimental Primary School in Qidong County in September 2021. == Life Experience == On October 28, 2015, he was born in [[Qidong County]], Hengyang City, [[Wikipedia:Hunan|Hunan Province]]. From March 2019, he studied in Taihetang Little Elves Kindergarten. In September 2020, he was transferred to Chuyuan Kindergarten (Lianhuayuan) in Qidong County to study in the first class of kindergarten. On July 6, 2021, he graduated from Chuyuan Kindergarten in [[Qidong County]]. [[zh:]]{{Celebrity|title=Wang Ziyu (Wang Jiaming's younger brother)|image=[[File:WangZiyu.jpg]]|chinese_name= |english_name=Wang Ziyu|gender=male|nationality={{cn}}|language=Chinese (Mandarin, Qidong dialect), English|minzu=Han|birthplace=[[Qidong County]], Hengyang City, Hunan Province|birthday ={{Birthdate|2009-08-25}}|hometown=[[Qidong County]], Hengyang City, Hunan Province|profession=student|height=growing|constellation=Virgo|representative_work=[[Steve's Space Adventure]] [[Black Coffin Carrier: Eating Bricks]]|nickname=|youtube=UCH0V4wPNGeKPCx9zzKr_VlA}} '''Wang Ziyu''' (Chinese name: ''''''), born on August 25, 2009 in [[Qidong County]], Hengyang City, [[Wikipedia:Hunan|Hunan Province]], is The younger brother of '''[[Wang Jiaming]]''', one of the founders of [[Jiaxing Radio Station]]. Representative works include "[[Awakening|Realization]]" (movie), "[[Desert Camel]]", "[[Light Chaser]]", "[[Big Fish]]", "[[Undersea]]" and so on. Wang Ziyu studied at Chuanshan Primary School in Qidong County from 2015 to 2021, and in Class 217 of Qidong Chengzhang from September 2021. == Some experiences == In September 2015, Wang Ziyu enrolled in Chuanshan Primary School in Qidong County. Around August 2017, Wang Ziyu won the first prize in the Hengyang Chess Competition. On August 7, 2019, Wang Ziyu went to Hengyang to get glasses with a prescription of 150 degrees. In January 2020, Wang Ziyu won the Outstanding Cadre Award for the winter vacation "English Sprint 100 Points" course. In January 2020, Wang Ziyu moved to a new house in Sanwang Garden in Qidong County. In April 2020, Wang Ziyu opened a YouTube channel called [[Wang Ziyu Funny Show]]. On May 2, 2021, Wang Ziyu recorded the latest cover single "[[Undersea]]", which was [[Wikipedia:Netease Cloud Music|Netease Cloud Music]] ranked first on the hot list. In June 2021, Wang Ziyu graduated from Chuanshan Primary School in Qidong County. In September 2021, he started studying at Chengzhang School in Qidong County.

{{Celebrity|image=LeiYangjuan.jpg|chinese_name=|english_name=Lei Yangjuan|gender=female|nationality={{China}}|language=Chinese|minzu=Han|birthplace=Qidong County, Hengyang City, Hunan Province |birthday={{Birthdate|1989-08-04}}|hometown=Hengyang City, Hunan Province|profession=administrator|height=160cm|caption=Lei Yangjuan is working. |representative_work=[[Bird Paradise]]|constellation=Leo}}
'''Lei Yangjuan''' (Chinese name: ''''''), born on {{Birthdate|1989-08-04}}, in '''[[Qidong County]], Hengyang City, [[Wikipedia:Hunan|Hunan Province]],''' China. On February 23, 2015, she married [[Wang Ximing]] and is the mother of '''[[Wang Zhaochu]]'''. Currently, she resides in [[wikipedia:Shenzhen|Shenzhen]], [[wikipedia:Guangdong|Guangdong Province]] with her husband and works at '''Delong Electrical Appliances Co., Ltd.''' in Shenzhen. ==Specific experience== Around 2010, Lei began working at Rui Bang Apparel Co., Ltd. in Dongguan, Guangdong, as a salesperson. Around 2013, she started working at Mei Ya Apparel Co., Ltd. in Shenzhen, where she worked in the human resources department as a management staff. From the first half of 2015 to May 2016, she took a leave of absence from work due to pregnancy and stayed at home to give birth to and care for her child. On November 2, 2019, a safety production management qualification certificate was obtained through the safety production knowledge and management ability assessment of Shenzhen Emergency Management Bureau. The certificate is valid for three years and was issued based on passing the assessment. The industry category is classified as non-high-risk production and operation. Around December 2019, she participated in the self-study examination of South China Normal University. In November 2021, she resigned from Mei Ya Apparel Co., Ltd. in Shenzhen and began working at Delong Electric Co., Ltd. in Shenzhen in the same month. See [[Wang Ximing]] for details. ==Representation== ===Cover of "[[:File:MV - Bird Paradisecover |Bird Paradise]]"=== [[File:MV - Bird Paradisecover ]] ===Wishes to Wang Zhaochu in his 7th Birthday=== [[File:720221028]] [[Category:Wang Ximing]] [[Category:Lei Yangjuan]] [[Category:Qidong]] [[Category:Wang Zhaochu]] [[Category:People]] [[zh:]] [[Category:Biography]] [[Category:NoCopy]] {{Navbox_Total}} {{PersonalInfoProtection}}

'''''Wang Ximing''''' (Chinese name: ''''''), was born on January 10, 1986 in Taihetang Town, [[Qidong County]], Hengyang City, [[Wikipedia:Hunan|Hunan Province]], native of '''Hengyang, [[Wikipedia:Hunan|Hunan Province]]'''. He graduated from the Industrial Design Department of '''Hunan University of Technology''' in 2009, and married with [[Lei Yangjuan]] on February 23, 2015. He is the father of [[Wang Zhaochu]] after Oct 28, 2015, and is currently living with Lei Yangjuan in ''' [[Wikipedia:Shenzhen|Shenzhen]], [[Wikipedia:Guangdong|Guangdong Province]]''', and working as a package design engineer at '''Shenzhen Comen Medical Equipment Co., Ltd.'''. Wang Ximing's hobbies include handicrafts, movies, and the electronic game DOTA2. ==Life experience== In September 1992, he enrolled in Taihetang Town Central Primary School, [[Qidong County]]. In September 1998, he enrolled in Chenglianxu Middle School in [[Qidong County]]. In September 2001, enrolled at Yuxian Middle School in [[Qidong County]]. In September 2004, enrolled at Dingxing Middle School in [[Qidong County]]. In September 2005, enrolled in the Industrial Design program at Hunan University of Technology. After graduating from university in 2009, worked as a market development/salesperson at Wahaha Sales Company in Yiyang City, [[Wikipedia:Hunan|Hunan Province]], from September of that year for a period of 7 months. In April 2010, switched to Ocean Paper Printing (Shenzhen) Co., Ltd., and was promoted to Packaging Engineer in 2013. In April 2020, switched to Chaoyang Electronics (Shenzhen) Co., Ltd. as a Packaging Engineer. On August 23, 2022, resigned from Chaoyang Electronics (Shenzhen) Co., Ltd. On August 31, 2022, started working at Shenzhen Comen Medical Equipment Co., Ltd. == Job Duties == === Hunan Wahaha Sales Yiyang Branch (2009.09-2010.03) === # Conducted market research and analyzed market demand. # Formulated detailed marketing plans and assisted in organizing exhibitions and sales promotion events. # Conducted on-site sales promotion and coordinated with terminal sales. # Employed other methods to increase the visibility and influence of new products and services of Wahaha in the market. === Ocean Paper Printing (Shenzhen) Co., Ltd. (2010.04-2020.04) === # Conducted physical testing of raw paper, corrugated paperboard, and finished products (including quantitative, thickness, moisture, ring pressure, edge pressure, puncture resistance, stacking, and dropping). # Designed and developed packaging and display plans that meet market demand and transportation safety requirements. # Provided professional packaging design recommendations based on cost. # Developed suitable packaging plans and created drawings according to product packaging requirements (including die-cutting, printing, and rendering). # Conducted packaging samples and assisted in the production of samples using the paper sample cutting machine. Analyzed packaging materials and technologies to improve production processes and techniques (including selection of molding methods, die-cutting and creasing technology, and corrugated box bonding technology). # Coordinated with relevant departments to supervise product quality (including specifications, dimensions, corrugation, adhesion, creasing, cutting, jointing, and printing quality). # Followed up with customer feedback in a timely manner to ensure that the packaging design and assembly meet customer requirements and standards. ==Character Events== Due to failing the college entrance exam in June 2004, repeated a year of high school at Dingxing Middle School in Qidong County starting in September of that year. In May 2014, participated in the national senior packaging engineer system learning and obtained the senior packaging engineer qualification certificate. In 2017, purchased a Huawei M3 tablet. On April 3, 2018, passed the third subject of the driver's license exam. In April 2019, Wang Ximing opened a [https://youtube.com/@wangximing1985 YouTube channel] and uploaded daily videos of Wang Zhaochu. In November 2019, participated in a 3-day training program on speech and virtue. On May 1, 2021, received a golden iPad. ==Marriage== In January 2013, Wang Ximing and [[Lei Yangjuan]] got engaged. On February 23, 2015 (the fifth day of the Chinese Lunar New Year), Wang Ximing and [[Lei Yangjuan]] held their [[Wang Ximing and Lei Yangjuan's Wedding|wedding ceremony]] at Yizhou Hotel in [[Qidong County]]. On October 28 of the same year, their son [[Wang Zhaochu]] was born. == Anecdotes == During his high school years, Wang Ximing was completely out of touch with reality and didn't consider his future. He would often spend his free time playing video games at nearby internet cafes, and sometimes even skipped class to do so. On the night before the national college entrance exam in June 2004, Wang Ximing was still immersed in an all-night gaming session at the internet cafe. After failing the exam, he repeated a year of high school at Dingxing High School and was able to score over 500 points on the second attempt, earning him admission to Hunan University of Technology's industrial design program. Wang Ximing's four years in college were both empty and happy. He played games all day, and the two classes a week he had were a breeze. His university experience taught him laziness, and sometimes when he returned home during breaks, his family found that his clothes had grown moldy and had a bad odor, even though he had only washed them a month before. Wang Ximing only studied one software program in college, and in the end, the only thing he did with his university computer was play games before eventually selling it to someone else. After graduating in 2009, Wang Ximing worked as a salesperson for Wahaha in Changsha, [[Wikipedia:Hunan|Hunan Province]]. Due to his unsuccessful work and lack of interest in sales, he left around 2011 and went to Shenzhen, where he found a stable job at a marine paper factory. Wang Ximing's love life has been full of ups and downs. In 2012, he reunited with his ex-girlfriend in Shenzhen, only to discover that she had been deceitful and unfaithful. His family advised him to break up with her, and while his ex-girlfriend was deeply upset at the time, Wang Ximing didn't feel much. In addition, the parents of Wang Ximing's ex-girlfriend felt that he was too introverted and not lively and despised her. Soon after his family's repeated persuasion, he eventually broke up with her and met [[Lei Yangjuan]] in 2013 through mutual friends and relatives. He quit smoking with the encouragement of Lei Yangjuan about a year after they met. After two years of dating in Shenzhen, they got married on February 23, 2015, at the Qidong Yizhou Hotel. ==Representation== ''[[Alien Revelation]]'' ''[[That Night, at Two O'Clock in the Morning in Shenzhen]]'' ==Related Videos== [[:File: - 1985-2004|Wang Ximing's Old Photos(1986~2004)]] [https://youtu.be/39BpOofS6X8 Wang Ximing and Lei Yangjuan Cycling] [https://youtu.be/0wR4AtFiyG0 Wang Ximing and Lei Yangjuan's wedding] [https://youtu.be/6-_wHEW-DzA Video of Wang Ximing's wedding reception] [[:File:MV|Lei Yangjuan & Wang Ximing Video Collection]] [[:File:2019|Wang Ximing, Wang Zhaochu and Wang Ziyu swim in Shuilifang Waterpark in 2019]] [[Wang Zhaochu's Seventh Birthday Wishes|Wang Zhaochu 7th Birthday Wishes in 2022]] [[zh:]] [[Category:Biography]] [[Category:People]] [[Category:Lei Yangjuan]] [[Category:Wang Ximing]] [[Category:NoCopy]] __NOEDITSECTION__ {{Navbox_Total}} {{PersonalInfoProtection}}

{{Wikipedia}}{{Stub}} [[zh:]] '''Qidong County''' is a county under the jurisdiction of Hengyang City. Located in the south of [[Wikipedia:Hunan|Hunan Province]], the People's Republic of China, in the Qishui Basin in the middle reaches of the Xiangjiang River, it is connected to Qiyang in the south, Shaodong and Hengyang in the north, Hengnan in the east, and Dong'an and Shaoyang in the west. It is also the county seat where [[Jiaxing Radio Station]] was founded and often filmed.
In 1952, Qidong County was established in the six northeastern districts of Qiyang, which was named Qidong because it was located in the east of Qiyang. The county has jurisdiction over 25 townships, streets, and offices, and 368 administrative villages (community neighborhood committees), with an area of 1872 square kilometers and a registered population of 1.058 million. It is the famous "Hometown of Yellow Flowers in China", "Hometown of Generals", "Hometown of Black Metal", and is currently the only "Hometown of Chinese Folk Art" in [[Wikipedia:Hunan|Hunan Province]]. The geographical coordinates are 11132161122010 east longitude, 2628127434 north latitude. ==History==
On April 25, 1952, Qiyang County was dissected and all of the seventh, eighth, ninth, and tenth districts of the original Qiyang County and most of the fifth and sixth districts were set aside to establish Qidong County. Due to the large area in the county Part of it is located in the east of Qiyang County, hence the name Qidong. Hongqiao is located in the county seat. The area under its jurisdiction includes Minyou, Guiyang, Sizhi, Jingyan, Sijing, Zhenzhong, Jingqing, Jinlan, Zhichang 9 townships and the northern half of Baolu Township in Qiyang County in the 38th year of the Republic of China (1949). When the county was established, it belonged to the Lingling Prefectural Area, since October 1952 it has been under the Shonan Administrative Office, since July 1954 it has been under the Hengyang Region, and since June 1983 it has been under the Hengyang City.
==Relationship with Jiaxing Radio Station==
[[Jiaxing Radio Station]] was founded in Qidong County, [[Wikipedia:Hunan|Hunan Province]] in 2014. [[Category:Qidong]]

{{Infobox | title1=Jiaxing Radio Station | image1=[[File:jiaxing.png|100px|center]] | title= | Simplified Chinese= | Traditional Chinese= | Founder=[[Wang Jiaming]], [[Guo Jingxing]] | English name=Jiaxing Official | Japanese name= | Country={{China}} | language=Simplified Chinese | type=YouTube channel | Establishment time=April 5, 2014 | Headquarters location = [[Qidong County]], Hengyang City, Hunan Province | Service Area=Global | URL=[https://odysee.com/@JiaxingVideos:f Odysee]
[http://v.qq.com/s/videoplus/353643993 Tencent]
[https://i.youku.com/jxvideoshow Youku]
[https://vimeo.com/jiaxingvideos Vimeo]
[https://www.dailymotion.com/guojingxing0905 Dailymotion] |caption1=The official logo of Jiaxing Radio Station (released in June 2014). |youtube=UC9XJQh5K_KtSssnBaW9iHyA|facebook=jiaxingvideos|Abbreviation=jiaxing|country={{CN}}}} '''Jiaxing Official ()''', also known as '''Jiaxing Videos''' or '''Jiaxing Video Album''', is a [[Wikipedia:YouTube|YouTube]] channel created and operated by a Chinese YouTuber Guo Jingxing since 2018. Its name '''Jiaxing''' came from its initial creators '''[[Wang Jiaming]]()'''(born: {{Birthdate|1999-09-24}}) and '''[[Guo Jingxing]]'''(born: {{Birthdate|1999-09-05}}) in April 5, 2014. It's now active with latest music album videos of '''''[[Wang Zhaochu]]()'''''(born: {{Birthdate|2015-10-28}}). The operator was claimed to be from [[Qidong]], Hunan in China, and all the videos are shot or made by Guo Jingxing in Hunan, China. Due to restriction of access to YouTube in China Mainland, most of the subscribers come from Singapore and Taiwan, while few Chinese people subscribe this channel. The channel uploads the daily vlog and music video of Wang Zhaochu, Wang Jiaming, [[Wang Ziyu]] and so on. Many of the videos were made before when this channel was created. And this channel has an odysee Channel duplicated in the early time of 2021, which can be seen [https://odysee.com/@JiaxingVideos:f here], making this YouTube channel a backup channel.
The channel was set up to reveal the daily life in Hunan, China and share some photos to record the daily life for memory. ==History== Since the foundation of Jiaxing Videos in April 2014, Wang and Guo start creating and uploading videos via some Chinese video platforms such as ''Youku'' and ''Tudou''. At first, they just create some videos of the latest news comment and telling jokes like ''Einstein and Chaplin's Story''. While few people in China mainland are interested in politics, they started creation of music and dance and afterwards, making music and funning videos dominated their channels for about 2 years. Their first [https://youtu.be/RujOVzzXVDM dancing video] was created on June 8, 2014.
In July 2015, Wang and Guo released their 2 episode talk show ''Wang&Guo Video Show''. In the first episode, they talked about the interesting things happened during ''Chinese National College Entrance Examination'' (also known as ''[[wikipedia:Gaokao|Gaokao]]'', one of the biggest examinations in China) during June 79 every year, while in the second episode they told some funny stories and little jokes and invite two guests in their program.
Since Jan 2017, Wang and Guo started creating music videos, and they released the first MV in Jan 16, 2017, which can be seen [https://youtu.be/uRrIJPeTAnU here]. The most viewed music video is ''[https://music.163.com/#/video?id=465FE9D06B5EDAB3551EA631FF452B3F 19-Years-Old]'' on ''Netease'' Music Platform released on Aug 10, 2018. Due to [[wikipedia:COVID-19|COVID-19]], Wang proposed to make an MV ''[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VTDv7xv0w_M Another Kind of Homesickness]'', which encourages the people and the doctors who fight through the coronavirus disease in Wuhan. Guo recorded Wang's younger brother's song ''[https://youtu.be/istxZmljAYI Desert Camel]'' on July 16, 2019 and become the milestone of making music through tuning (on Wang Ziyu's music), which becomes an indispensable part of Jiaxing Video Album.
After the birth of Wang Zhaochu (Hereinafter referred to as WZC) in 2015, recording and making WZC's video an important part. The most famous video of WZC is ''[https://youtu.be/Yp-Pgbg8cQQ Two Tigers]''. All of WZC's videos have been collected [https://www.youtube.com/@jiaxingvideos/playlists?view=50&sort=dd&shelf_id=4 here]. ==Features== Since the development of Jiaxing Videos for about 3 years, this channel has developed some features: *Most of the videos are created, shot, or made by Guo Jingxing in Qidong, It has some features made by Guo and most of the videos doesn't contain Guo but other people. Wang Zhaochu is the most photographed person.
*The main and the most original playlist of this channel can be seen in the playlist ''[https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLr2zN-4ce5vnkS2nFlfiyVcdO-rcNnk22 Jiaxing Official Channel]'', which has collected the videos they've made since 2012 in time order. All of the main videos by Wang and Guo are collected in the playlist [https://www.youtube.com/@jiaxingvideos/playlists?view=50&shelf_id=1 page].

Some Nintendo games(Super Mario Bros., Bug's Bunny Fun House, Rainbow Islands) played by Wang Jiaming in 2012 are the most ancient videos.

{{Wikipedia}}'''Hengyang No.8 Middle School''' (Chinese: '''''''''' ) is located in Hengyang, [[Wikipedia:Hunan|Hunan Province]], China No. 81, Huangbai Road, Hengyang City, is a public school in Hengyang City and one of the model middle schools in Hunan Province. In 2012, it was awarded the first batch of youth clean government cultural education bases in Hengyang City. In 2013, it was rated as an ecological civilization demonstration school in Hunan Province by the Hunan Provincial Department of Education. In 2016, it was awarded "2016 Shengyuan Middle School" by Tsinghua University. [[Guo Jingxing]] studied in Class 423 of Hengyang Eighth Middle School from 2013 to 2016. ==School Culture== School motto: from high to strict, seeking truth and beauty
Spirit: self-confidence, self-improvement, unity and forge ahead, dare to be the first, and create first-class bravely
Teaching style: Rigorous and professional, cooperative and innovative
Style of study: erudite and prudent, discerning interrogation ==Awards== The No. 8 Middle School of Hengyang City has won the honors of "National Top 100 Middle Schools" and "Leader of Key Middle Schools in Hunan Province". ==official site== [http://www.hysbz.com Hengyang Eighth Middle School] ==Outstanding Alumni== ===Politics=== Among the alumni of No. 8 Middle School in Hengyang City, Wang Xiaofeng served as Deputy Secretary of the Hunan Provincial Party Committee, Secretary of the Provincial Party Committee and Governor of Hainan Province, and Hu Dan (Hu Qinchun) served as Deputy Director of the Research Department of the Party History Institute of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China.
Liao Daiguang served as the vice mayor of Yiyang City, party secretary and principal of Hunan Urban Construction Institute.

Jens Bergenstein (2011-present)|art=Markus Toivonen|music=C418, Lena Raine|mode=single player, multiplayer|release_date=November 18, 2011 |official_website=https://www.minecraft.net/en-us/}} '''Minecraft''' (commonly known as "'''MC'''" in mainland China) is a sandbox game developed by Swedish game designer Markus Alexei Poisson (Notch) in Java language , the alpha version was released in 2009, and then officially released by the Swedish company Mojang in November 2011, and Jens Bergenstein (Jeb) was responsible for the main development. Players play in a random procedurally generated 3D world based on textured cubes. Other features in the game include exploring the world, gathering resources, synthesizing items, and survival adventures. There are many modes in the game. In survival mode, players must maintain life and collect resources to build their own world; in creative mode, players have unlimited resources and can fly, and most players will use this mode to build large buildings; in adventure mode, players Play on maps customized by other players. The Java Edition of the game is known for its powerful third-party expansion modules (mods), which can add various new objects, characters, and functions to the game.
"Minecraft" has received unanimous praise from the industry, winning many awards and honors. In September 2014, Microsoft announced the acquisition of Mojang and the intellectual property rights of the game for US$2.5 billion, and the acquisition was completed two months later. In May 2016, NetEase announced that it was the agent of the Chinese version of "My World", and in August 2017, the public beta was launched.
As of 2020, Minecraft has 200 million sales volume and 126 million monthly active users on various platforms, and is comparable to the imitation game of ROBLOX machine cubes, and is the best-selling video game in history.
==Relationship with Jiaxing Radio Station==
[[Jiaxing Radio Station]]'s younger brother [[Wang Ziyu]], one of the founders of [[Jiaxing Radio Station]], was once an obsessed player of the game "Minecraft". Wang Ziyu used [[Guo Jingxing]]s mobile phone to download Minecraft from 2017 to 2020, and also used Guo Jingxings computer to play Minecraft and recorded multiple game videos and sent them to Jiaxing Broadcasting Stations YouTube, on Youku channel.
In 2019, Wang Ziyu wrote a Minecraft movie script "[[Steve's Cosmic Adventure]]", and at the same time made a short Minecraft short film with Guo Jingxing, which tells the story of Steve in the forest Cutting down trees, and being blown up by creepers, Steve came to the local high-level castle and used a computer to talk to [[Wang Ziyu]].
==Wang Ziyu Funny Show== [[Wang Ziyu]] continuously recorded Minecraft game commentary videos from April to June 2020, and uploaded them to the YouTube channel [[Wang Ziyu Funny Show]]. Wang Ziyu uses Minecraft 1.7. Version 10 (the client of the Duck Exchange Club), and configure various additional game mods.
== Wang Zhaochu playing minecraft == [[Wang Zhaochu]] is also an obsessed player of Minecraft. Wang Zhaochu's favorite prop in Minecraft is the energy absorption gun, and he likes building houses, digging holes, using TNT and flint. Wang Zhaochu likes to watch Guo Jingxing use a nuclear bomb to blow up a big crater in Minecraft.

[[zh:]]{{Celebrity|title=Wang Jiaming|image=WangJiaming.jpg|chinese_name=|english_name=Wang Jiaming|gender=male|nationality={{cn}}|language=Chinese(Mandarin, Qidong dialect), English |minzu=Han |birthplace=[[Qidong County]], Hengyang City, Hunan Province|birthday={{Birthdate|1999-09-24}}|hometown=Qidong County, Hengyang City, Hunan Province|profession=graduate student|college= [https://zh.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E6%A1%82%E6%9E%97%E7%90%86%E5%B7%A5%E5%A4%A7%E5%AD%A6 Guilin University of Science and Technology]|height=173cm|weight=60kg|constellation=Libra|achievements=First Prize of 2018 "Internet +" Innovation Competition
2022 Guilin University of Technology Postgraduate National Scholarship|email=1638382633@qq.com|caption=Wang Jiaming is filming the MV of "An Ordinary Day". |representative_work="[[Wang Ziyu tours Siming Mountain]]"
"Grandma's Life"|political_status=CCP member|qq=1638382633|wechat=dgdgwang}} '''Wang Jiaming''' (Chinese name: ''''''), was born on September 24, 1999 in [[Qidong County]], Hengyang City, [[Wikipedia:Hunan|Hunan Province]], he is a native in Qidong, Hengyang, Hunan, and is one of the founders of [[Jiaxing Radio Station]]. Wang Jiaming grew up in [[Qidong County]], with elder cousin brother [[Wang Ximing]] and elder cousin sister Wang Ting. In 2009, Wang Jiaming's younger brother [[Wang Ziyu]] was born. Wang Jiaming passed the [[wikipedia:Gaokao|National College Entrance Examination]] in 2016 and was admitted to [https://zh.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E6%A1%82%E6%9E%97%E7%90%86%E5%B7%A5%E5%A4%A7%E5%AD%A6 Guilin University of Technology] majoring in mechanical engineering and automation, moved into [[Qidong County]] Sanwang Garden built in 2018 in January 2020 Xinwu, who passed the 2020 National Graduate Admissions Examination, was admitted to Guilin University of Technology, majoring in computer science and technology, to study for a master's degree. Representative works include "[[Little Apple]]" (2014), "[[Once You]]", "[[Nineteen Years Old]]", "[[Ordinary Day]]" and so on. Obtained in September 2022 National Scholarship in [https://zh.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E6%A1%82%E6%9E%97%E7%90%86%E5%B7%A5%E5%A4%A7%E5%AD%A6 Guilin University of Technology].<ref>It is easy for you| It is not easy for these graduate students to win the National Scholarship! https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/dV9CuBjGZ87FaviTPuL2qw</ref>
==Life Experience== On September 24, 1999, Wang Jiaming was born in [[Qidong County]], Hengyang City, [[Wikipedia:Hunan|Hunan Province]], and lived opposite Zaoshuyuan Market on Chujie Road.
In September 2004, Wang Jiaming enrolled in Jinwa Primary School in Qidong County.
In September 2006, enrolled in Qidong County No. 7 Primary School.
In September 2010, enrolled in Chujie Middle School in Qidong County.
In September 2011, due to the reorganization of Chujie Middle School into Chuanshan Experimental Primary School, I chose to transfer to the No. 2 Middle School of Hongqiao Town, Qidong County.
In September 2013, enrolled in the No. 2 Middle School of Qidong County.
In June 2016, he participated in the National College Entrance Examination (National College Entrance Examination).
In September 2016, admitted to [https://zh.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E6%A1%82%E6%9E%97%E7%90%86%E5%B7%A5%E5%A4%A7%E5%AD%A6 Guilin University of Technology], began studying for a bachelor's degree in mechanical engineering and automation.
In December 2017, passed the National College English Test Band 4.
In December 2017, participated in the Guangxi College Students Mechanical Design Competition and won the first prize.
In May 2018, participated in the National Undergraduate Internet + Innovation Competition and won the first prize.
In June 2019, passed the National College English Test Band-6.
In December 2019, I participated in [https://zh.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E8%80%83%E7%A0%94 National Postgraduate Admissions Examination], and the applicant institution was Hunan Normal University.
In January 2020, moved to a new house in Sanwang Garden in [[Qidong County]].
In June 2020, graduated from Guilin University of Technology.
In September 2020, he began to study for a master's degree in computer science and technology from Guilin University of Technology.
On May 21, 2021, the first dose of the new crown vaccine will be vaccinated.
In September 2022, [https://zh.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E6%A1%82%E6%9E%97%E7%90%86%E5%B7%A5%E5%A4%A7%E5%AD%A6 Guilin University of Technology] National Scholarship for Graduate Students.
==Applying for Chinese Communist Party Experience== In October 2016, I submitted an application for joining the party, but was rejected because I was under 18 years old.
In October 2017, he submitted the application for joining the party for the second time and was successfully elected as a party activist. However, he was disqualified as a party activist because he failed the exam in February 2018.
In October 2020, he submitted an application for joining the party for the third time, but was defeated in the voting and talking sessions.
In March 2021, submitted the application for joining the party for the fourth time, and was successfully selected as an active member of the party. It is expected to be selected as a probationary member of the Communist Party of China in December 2021.
==Research Achievements==
(1) SCI paper: Wang J, Xie X, Cheng X, et al. Improved Density Peaking Algorithm for Community Detection Based on Graph Representation Learning[J]. Comput. Syst. Sci. Eng., 2022, 43(3): 997-1008.
(2) Chinese core papers: Chen Chaoquan, Wang Jiaming, Xie Xiaolan. Improved Density Peak Clustering by Combining Manifold Distance and Label Propagation[J]. Science Technology and Engineering, 2022, 22(10): 4011-4018.
(3) Papers published in English general journals: Wang J, Xie X, Wang B. CTO ORDER CLUSTERING FOR ELECTRONIC PRODUCTS BASED ON WORD VECTORS[J]. IETI Transactions on Engineering Research and Practice, 2022, 6(1): 29-37.
(4) Invention patent: Patent number: CN202210940841.5 Patent status: Application and acceptance Patent name: A personalized custom order anomaly detection system based on LOF algorithm
==Research project==
(1) Participating project: GCN-LSTM-based multi-sensor data fusion research provincial project
(2) Participating projects: OPM model-oriented smart service platform for electronic smart manufacturing industry provincial project
==Contest Award==
(1) First Prize in the Big Data Track of the Second Guangxi Undergraduate Artificial Intelligence Design Competition
(2) The third prize in the deep learning track of the 3rd Guangxi Undergraduate Artificial Intelligence Design Competition
(3) The 6th "Yixue Cup" National College Students' English Vocabulary and Comprehensive Ability Competition Provincial First Prize
(4) Third Prize in the English Translation Competition of the Third National College Innovation English Challenge
(5) First Prize of the National Undergraduate Artificial Intelligence Knowledge Contest
